bucket_trades retrieves open high low close (OHLC) data for the specified symbol/timeframe.

bucket_trades(
  binSize = "1m",
  partial = "false",
  symbol = "XBT",
  filter = NULL,
  columns = NULL,
  count = 1000,
  start = NULL,
  reverse = "true",
  startTime = NULL,
  endTime = NULL
)

Arguments

binSize

Time interval to bucket by. Must be one of: 1m, 5m, 1h or 1d.
partial

If true, will send in-progress (incomplete) bins for the current time period.
symbol

Instrument symbol. You can also send a timeframe, e.g. XBT:quarterly
filter

Generic table filter. Send JSON key/value pairs, such as "'key':'value'".
columns

Array of column names to fetch. If omitted, will return all columns.
count

Number of results to fetch. Maximum of 1000 (the default) per request.
start

Starting point for results.
reverse

If true, will sort results newest first (default = "true").
startTime

Starting date filter for results.
endTime

Ending date filter for results.

Value

`bucket_trades` returns a data.frame containing open high low close data for the specified time interval

Details

The API will only return 1000 rows per call. If the desired timeframe requires more than one API call, consider using map_bucket_trades.
